		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That looks like the link may be useful.  I also purchased a book called <em>Programming the 6502</em> by Rodnay Zaks.  That's a pretty good book.  It usually on eBay for pretty cheap.
<br />
<br />I can't seem to find the link right now, but there's a nice .html page of the 6502 (or 6500 family?) that has all that kind of thing documented.  Also, check <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.6502.org/">http://www.6502.org/</a><!-- m --> , there's alot of cool stuff there.  Hope this helps.

		

