		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Really Good Books i Found are "6502 Software Design",  "Programming and Interfacing the 6502 w/ Experiements", and "Programming a MIcrocomputer: 6502".  The first two are a little more advanced but if you  want to learn about memory mapping "Programming and Interfacing the 6502 w/ Experiements" has a small section on it in which you can interface OP AMPs for Music Synthesis.  "Programming a Microcomputer: 6502" has a cool little project in which you can make a musical piano. But Basically "Programming the 6502"  is great reference guide,  all his other book kinda suck unless you want to learn AI.  Ive gotten many books and these are basiclly the coolest ones ive ever come by.  Does anyone know of any other 6502 books that have music synthesis as a topic?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


